{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567053","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567053"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:53:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:53:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18924"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18924","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18924"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.67,0.27,0.01,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11657"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80405"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11657","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11657"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18924"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65681"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11367"},{"type":"tags","id":"11368"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27430"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27431"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80405","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80405"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA public hospital is reviewing its resource allocation policies. The hospital aims to maximise health outcomes while maintaining financial sustainability. The review committee is considering various approaches to healthcare resource management.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following approaches best promotes efficient healthcare resource usage?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Providing all available treatments to every patient","Basing clinical decisions on evidence-based guidelines","Implementing risk-stratified diagnostic pathways","Restricting access to specialist services","Implementing mandatory minimum hospital stays"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most efficient approach to healthcare resource usage involves \u003Cstrong\u003Ebasing clinical decisions on evidence-based guidelines\u003C/strong\u003E. This ensures that interventions are both clinically appropriate and cost-effective, leading to optimal health outcomes while avoiding unnecessary resource consumption.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProviding all available treatments to every patient\u003C/strong\u003E - This approach is wasteful and potentially harmful, ignoring both clinical appropriateness and cost-effectiveness\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImplementing risk-stratified diagnostic pathways\u003C/strong\u003E - While this appears systematic, it may not incorporate the latest evidence and could lead to rigid, inefficient protocols\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERestricting access to specialist services\u003C/strong\u003E - This may lead to delayed diagnosis and treatment, resulting in poorer outcomes and higher long-term costs\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImplementing mandatory minimum hospital stays\u003C/strong\u003E - This removes clinical decision-making flexibility and may keep patients in hospital longer than necessary\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEvidence-based guidelines help clinicians make informed decisions about diagnostic tests and treatments, considering both clinical effectiveness and resource implications. This approach promotes high-quality care while maintaining sustainable healthcare resource usage.\u003C/p\u003E","option